  <h1>Welcome to the Orange Cats website!</h1>
  <p>Here you will find information about orange cats, including their history, characteristics, and interesting facts.</p>

  <h2>History of Orange Cats</h2>
  <p>Orange cats have been beloved companions for humans for thousands of years. The ancient Egyptians revered cats of all colors, including orange ones, and often depicted them in their art and mythology.</p>

  <h2>Characteristics of Orange Cats</h2>
  <p>Orange cats are known for their striking coats, which can range from pale peach to deep auburn. They often have bright green or gold eyes and a distinctive meow. Orange cats are typically friendly and affectionate, and they make great companions.</p>

  <h2>Interesting Facts About Orange Cats</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Orange cats are typically male. In fact, about 80% of orange cats are male.</li>
    <li>Orange cats are often associated with the Halloween season because of their orange color.</li>
    <li>Famous orange cats include Garfield, Marmalade from the musical Cats, and Crookshanks from the Harry Potter series.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Conclusion</h2>
  <p>We hope you have enjoyed learning about orange cats on our website. If you have any questions or would like to share your own experiences with orange cats, please feel free to contact us.</p>
